Defendant Javarlowe V Banks in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Danielle Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant sentenced to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 6 (six) days time served.

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.  Huber privileges for work, school and childcare.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-  Court ordered the defendant to serve 30 days (STRAIGHT TIME) in the House of Correction.  This time is stayed to be used at the probation agent's discretion.
- Court ordered defendant to pay all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, including DNA surcharge.  Court ordered a payment plan in the amount of $20.00 per month with the first payment due on 11/22/15 and additional payments due the 22ND of each month thereafter.  If there are any missed payments any remaining balance will be due FORTHWITH and an immediate entry of a civil judgment is ordered by the court.
- Seek and maintain fulltime employment.  Until fulltime employment is found, defendant is to start his job search at 6:00 am each day and should submit at least 3 employment applications per day.
- Participate in GED/HSED program.
- Paternity action to be completed, if not already done for his child.  Defendant is to report to the Child Support Office office before 12:00 pm 10/22/15 to begin the paternity action.
- Comply with any child support orders.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done.
- Fine is set at ZERO.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: firearm possession and voting.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant.

Expungement: 
For the reasons placed on the record, the Court granted the Defense request for expungement upon successfully completion of probation, including maintaining fulltime employment and completing his GED.

Defendant Javarlowe V Banks in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Brandon Wigley on behalf of Danielle Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNT 1 :

The defendant was advised of his Constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, the victim  and the defendant.   Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 3 business days in advance of the sentencing.
